FBIS4-65949 "drweu102_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 SPAIN Defense Minister Sees Russian Role in Partnership Defense Minister Sees Russian Role in Partnership LD2505191194 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505191194 Madrid RNE International Spanish BFN [Excerpts] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev asked the representatives of NATO member countries meeting in Brussels for a consulting mechanism on European and global security issues which would function on a regular basis as well as during crises. Our Brussels correspondent Nacho Hernandez reports: [Begin Hernandez recording] [passage omitted] According to Spanish Defense Minister Julian Garcia Vargas, Moscow's initiative would be appropriate for the Partnership for Peace put forward by NATO. [Vargas] I think it does have its place. If you take into consideration what we were saying yesterday--and what is common knowledge relayed by all the media--that France.... [pauses] excuse me, that Russia is a superpower, naturally it seems good and is positive for all concerned. [end recording]
